          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Calls for honoring the 231st anniversary of the enactment of the Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom on Religious Freedom Day, January 16, 2017.</p> <p>Affirms that: </p> <ul> <li> religious freedom includes the right of individuals of any faith and individuals of no faith to live, work, associate, and worship in accordance with their beliefs;</li> <li> all people of the United States can be unified in supporting religious freedom because it is a fundamental human right; and </li> <li> the American people will remain forever unshackled in matters of faith.</li> </ul>]]></text>
